Part D: Practical Implications

1. Propositional encoding for a 100x100 warehouse is not very practical due to its large number of clauses for a constraint and slower time to encode.
2. Restrictions that would make FOL inference tractable includes Function-free FOL which makes the domain bounded and Horn clauses which allows forward and backward chaining for improved effiency.
3. A hybrid approach works where FOL does general rules and logic compactly with little clauses while propositional logic can access a smaller localized section to efficiently encode.